===Etymology===
Old Norse ''oddi'' (''third or additional number''), which comes from ''[[oddr]]'' (''point of a weapon'') via an intermediate meaning of "[[triangle]]". The original meaning is "left over".
===Adjective===
'''odd''' ({{compar}}: '''odder''', {{superl}}: '''oddest''')

#[[strange]], [[unusual]].
#{{arithmetic}} (''no comparative or superlative'') Not [[divisible]] by [[two]].
#(''rare'') But for the odd exception. <!--self-referential definition?-->
#[[left over]], [[remain]]ing when the rest have been [[grouped]]
#:''the odd one out''
#[[casual]], [[irregular]].
#:''odd jobs''
#(''in combination with a number'') [[about]], [[approximately]].
#:''There were thirty-odd people in the room.''

